    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex> be the projection of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_0]]></fr:tex>;
      applying <fr:ref
addr="sga1-i.7.6"
href="sga1-i.7.6.xml"
taxon="Theorem"
number="I.7.6" /> to the étale local homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A_0\to  B_0]]></fr:tex> of local rings of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0]]></fr:tex>, we obtain an isomorphism
      <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[         \begin {aligned}           B_0 &= (C_0)_{\mathfrak {n}_0}         \\C_0 &= A_0[t]/F_0A_0[t]         \end {aligned}       ]]></fr:tex>
      where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F_0]]></fr:tex> is a monic polynomial, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {n}_0]]></fr:tex> is a maximal ideal of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C_0]]></fr:tex> not containing the class of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F'_0(t)]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C_0]]></fr:tex>.
      Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be the local ring of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> be a monic polynomial in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A[t]]]></fr:tex> that gives <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F_0]]></fr:tex> under the surjective homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\to  A_0]]></fr:tex> (we lift the coefficients of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F_0]]></fr:tex>), and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C=A[t]/FA[t]]]></fr:tex>, with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {n}]]></fr:tex> the maximal ideal of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> given by the inverse image of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {n}_0]]></fr:tex> under the natural epimorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C\to  C\otimes _A A_0=C_0]]></fr:tex>.
      Let
      <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[         B = C_\mathfrak {n}.       ]]></fr:tex>
      It is immediate, by construction and by <fr:ref
addr="sga1-i.7.1"
href="sga1-i.7.1.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="I.7.1" />, that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is étale over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, and that we have an isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B\otimes _A A_0=A_0]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

    <fr:p>We know that there exists a <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>-scheme <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> of finite type, along with a point <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[z]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_z]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-isomorphic to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>;
      since the latter is étale over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A=\mathcal {O}_y]]></fr:tex>, we can (by taking <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> to be small enough) assume that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is étale over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>.
      Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X'_0=X\times _Y Y_0]]></fr:tex>.
      Then the local ring of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[z]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X'_0]]></fr:tex> can be identified with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_z\otimes _A A_0=B\otimes _A A_0]]></fr:tex>, and is thus isomorphic to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B_0]]></fr:tex>.
      This isomorphism is defined by an isomorphism from a neighbourhood <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_0]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> to a neighbourhood of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[z]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X'_0]]></fr:tex>, and we can assume this to be identical to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X'_0]]></fr:tex> by taking <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> to be small enough.</fr:p>
